trend_summary: Across the sequence, the landscape remains largely agricultural, but a slow ribbon of growth appears along the northâ€“south highway and around the small town core: light industrial sheds, a few new residential blocks and minor road extensions replace scattered fields while forest belts thicken along waterways. Overall fabric is still mostly rural and low-density.
notable_changes: Industrial park expands beside the main highway interchange, adding several large white-roofed buildings.
New residential subdivision grids emerge west of the town core, replacing patchwork fields.
Highway corridor shows widened rights-of-way and added slip roads.
Several large central fields transition from active cultivation to mixed grass or fallow cover.
Riparian tree cover increases, especially along the southern stream valley.
